If you're still getting the wl not found error after installing the broadcom-sta-dkms package, you can try the following steps:

Open a terminal and run the following command to update your package list:

sql
Copy code
sudo apt update
Run the following command to install the firmware-b43-installer package:

Copy code
sudo apt install firmware-b43-installer
Reboot your system and check if the wireless interface is available by running the iwconfig command:

Copy code
iwconfig
If the wireless interface is still not available, you can try the following:

Open a terminal and run the following command to update your package list:

sql
Copy code
sudo apt update
Run the following command to install the linux-headers package that matches your kernel version:

bash
Copy code
sudo apt install linux-headers-$(uname -r)
Download the hybrid-v35_64-nodebug-pcoem-6_30_223_271.tar.gz file from the Broadcom website:

ruby
Copy code
wget https://www.broadcom.com/content/dam/broadcom/support/oem/HP/broadcom-wl-6.30.223.271+bdcom-0.tar.gz
Extract the contents of the downloaded file:

Copy code
tar -zxvf broadcom-wl-6.30.223.271+bdcom-0.tar.gz
Change to the extracted directory:

bash
Copy code
cd broadcom-wl-6.30.223.271+bdcom
Run the following command to build and install the wl module:

go
Copy code
make && sudo make install
Reboot your system and check if the wireless interface is available by running the iwconfig command:

Copy code
iwconfig
If none of the above solutions work, it's possible that your wireless card is not compatible with Linux or there may be a hardware issue.
